spans.text: Ah Cynthia ! sweeter than the breath of morn , Soft as the gentle breath that fans at eve , Of thee bereft how shall I live forlorn
bedecked with many a flower , Where maple-tufts exclude the beam of day
many a flower , Where maple-tufts exclude the beam of day
lavish Spring her smiles around has cast
laughing hours , Which led me up the roseate steep of youth
laughing hours , Which led me up the roseate steep of youth
the curling breeze , or gilded fly That idly wantons in the noontide air , Was not so free
heave my breast If ever my cheek was conscious of a tear , Till Cynthia came and robbed my soul of rest
that shuns the gilded bed , With smiling Peace
The woodland nymphs , and gentle fays , at eve Forth from the dripping cave and mossy dell ,
the choicest rolls of ancient Time
me that stubborn love disdains to yield
forsake me in the jocund field
